{"article_id":"jqXon8ImXZ9ulqpp","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The US economy roared into 2017 ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"adding 238,000 jobs in January and 235,000 jobs in February .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"But with the Labor Department 's March unemployment report ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"released on Friday ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that strong start seems to be sputtering .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"Economists had expected","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"that hiring would cool off ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"projecting an increase of about 180,000 new jobs .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"But the Bureau of Labor Statistics ' s establishment survey fell short of even that projection ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"finding","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that total nonfarm payroll increased by just 98,000 jobs last month .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"( Its household survey showed a 326,000-person drop in unemployment ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"but economists consider the establishment survey ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"which has a larger sample size","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and focuses on employers ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to be a more accurate measure . )","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"Last month ' s hiring dip was likely felt by many of the 7.2 million Americans currently unemployed .","depth":3},{"id":17,"text":"But","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"while March ' s employment results were disappointing ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"they don ' t mean","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that the nation 's long-running pattern of job growth has ended .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"it 's a little bit surprising ...","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that it came in as low as 98","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"[ thousand ] , \"","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"says Elise Gould , senior economist at the Economic Policy Institute","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"( EPI ) .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"\" I expect","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that it 's a slip ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"and that we will see more on-trend numbers next month . \"","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"In a phone interview with The , Dr. Gould identifies one possible","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"- and surprising -","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"reason for the drop .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"The projections","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"economists use ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"she explains ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"are \" not built","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"to take deviations in the weather . \"","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"The weather has seen plenty of deviations from the norm this winter , from record-breaking warmth in February to a major Northeast blizzard in early March .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Both could have shifted economic trends ;","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"warmer-than-usual winter weather , for instance , means","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"that construction sites can stay open","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"and that more potential shoppers and home-buyers may feel inclined to venture outside .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"On the flipside , a big snowstorm can close workplaces","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"and put a damper on those activities .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"In an email to the Monitor , Mark Hamrick , Bankrate.com ' s senior economic analyst , noted","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"that \" construction employment slowed in March","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"with 6,000 jobs added","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"after nearly 10 times that number reported hired the month before .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"Weather may have whipped some of these numbers around a bit . \"","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Gould also points out","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"that last month ' s big storm \" happened during a reference week \" for the BLS survey ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"and adds ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"\" there 's some history","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"of March being softer in general \" for job growth .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"For instance , March hiring also slacked off in 2016 and 2015 ,","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"The New York Times reports .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"To be sure ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"weather isn ' t the only factor","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"affecting job seekers ' prospects .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Structural changes in the economy , such as automation and outsourcing , are continuing to erase yesterday ' s low-skilled positions .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"Hamrick highlighted one instance of this trend","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"in discussing the March report .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"A wave of recent chain-store closings","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"- driven by competition from e-commerce firms -","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"drove a loss of nearly 30,000 retail jobs .","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"In a sign","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"that many Americans still don ' t see reason","depth":16},{"id":68,"text":"to even look for jobs ,","depth":16},{"id":69,"text":"the labor force participation rate remained unchanged from February at 63 percent","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"- more than 4 percentage points below its 2000 levels .","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"This smaller pool of potential workers","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"- not just new hiring -","depth":15},{"id":73,"text":"is helping keep the unemployment rate at a remarkably low 4.5 percent .","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"And","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"while those with jobs saw their wages increase by an average of 2.7 percent ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"Hamrick says","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"that ' s below the \" 3 percent level","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"that we ' d associate with a stronger recovery , \" or a \" tight \" labor market .","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"Gould agrees .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"`` I think","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"we 're still seeing a situation","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"where employers do n't have to ... make huge [ wage ] increases","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"to attract and retain the workers","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"they want . ''","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"Despite these less-than-encouraging numbers , it ' s worth remembering that the United States has already come a long way since the Great Recession .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"According to the EPI ' s autopilot economy tracker ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"the share of the prime-age population","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"( ages 25-54 )","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"with a job has reached 78.5 percent","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"- its highest level since September 2008 , and well above the 74.8 percent","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"it hit in December 2009 .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":93,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":94,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":95,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":96,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":97,"text":"At least for the moment , though , that recovery seems to have hit a slowdown .","depth":3},{"id":98,"text":"\" While we 're moving towards full employment , \"","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"Gould says ,","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"\" we are still not there yet . \"","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":201,"left":192,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":192,"left":116,"right":191,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":105,"right":115,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":102,"right":104,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":102,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":103,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":103,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":107,"right":114,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN